e possibly lacking metadata. Also, I need to ensure that the package class `MockitoRunnerTarget` starts with \\\"Mockito.\\\" Lastly, I might need to check on untracked files.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "Implemented coverage for `org.mockito.internal.runners.util.RunnerProvider`.\n\nChanges made:\n- Added dedicated test file:\n  - `tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/org_mockito/mockito_core/RunnerProviderTest.java`\n- Updated test project support files required by the new public API path:\n  - `tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/build.gradle`\n    - Added JUnit 4 dependency for `JUnitCore` / `MockitoJUnitRunner`.\n  - `tests/src/org.mockito/mockito-core/5.0.0/src/test/java/module-info.java`\n    - Added `requires junit`.\n    - Opened the test package to `junit`.\n\nThe new test exercises `RunnerProvider` through Mockito’s public JUnit 4 runner API by invoking `JUnitCore.runClasses(...)` on a nested `@RunWith(MockitoJUnitRunner.StrictStubs.class)` test class. This path reaches the reflective `Class.forName`, constructor lookup, and constructor instantiation call sites in `RunnerProvider`.\n\nI did not run compilation or tests, per instruction.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_06b727647170a1e3016a2c174d09048197a6012fef24e404ea\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 438, "output": 1128, "cacheRead": 29184, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 30750, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1781274419403, "responseId": "resp_06b727647170a1e3016a2c1733ff78819781eda2570950ed79"}}
